memberdef.name: m_TextBlock_06
memberdef.initializer:
= "<align=center><style=H1><#ffffff><u>Multiple<#80f0ff> Alignment</color> per text object</u></color></style></align><line-height=2em>
" + "</line-height> The <<#ffffa0>align</color>> tag in TextMesh<#40a0ff>Pro</color> provides the ability to control the alignment of lines and paragraphs which is essential when working with text.
" + "<align=left> You may want some block of text to be<#80f0ff>left aligned</color> <<#ffffa0>align=<#80f0ff>left</color></color>> which is sort of the standard.</align>
" + "<style=Quote><#ffffa0>"Using <#80f0ff>Center Alignment</color> <<#ffffa0>align=<#80f0ff>center</color></color>> for a title or displaying a quote is another good example of text alignment."</color></style>
" + "<align=right><#80f0ff>Right Alignment</color> <<#ffffa0>align=<#80f0ff>right</color></color>> can be useful to create contrast between lines and paragraphs of text.
" + "<align=justified><#80f0ff>Justified Alignment</color> <<#ffffa0>align=<#80f0ff>justified</color></color>> results in text that is flush on both the left and right margins. Used well, justified type can look clean and classy.
" + "<style=Quote><align=left><#ffffa0>"Text formatting and alignment has a huge impact on how people will read and perceive your text."</color>
" + "<size=65%><align=right> -Stephan Bouchard</style>"
